# RAG exam-document extraction

Follow `docs/rag-extraction-spec.md` and `src/lib/rag/schemas.ts`.

## Non-negotiable rules

1. Never assume `one page = one question`. A page may contain zero, one, or many questions; a question may span regions or pages.
2. Preserve exact source wording in `versions.source` (spelling mistakes, grammar, abbreviations, uncertainty like “I think”). Do not silently improve.
3. Every question must have `origin: "extracted" | "reconstructed" | "generated"`. Never present generated text as extracted.
4. Associate images only when required to answer — not merely because they share a page with a question.
5. Do not generate MCQs during extraction. Generation uses `GENERATION_SYSTEM_PROMPT` in a separate step (`generate-question` task).
6. Validate all outputs with Zod (`questionSchema`, `pageExtractionResultSchema`, `documentExtractionResultSchema`).
7. When answers conflict or are uncertain, preserve evidence and require review — never invent a confirmed source answer.
8. The review UI must keep source / normalized / quiz-ready distinguishable, and label reconstructed/generated questions.
